The Eastern Cape has recorded the highest number of cases this summer with 17 people dead. JOHANNESBURG - As the death toll in initiations schools rose to 23 this month, the Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Department has called on communities to notify authorities about bogus initiation schools.The department expressed concern and regret at the loss of life, saying it will continue to work together with various organisations to ensure the safe return of initiates.The Eastern Cape has recorded the highest number of cases this summer with 17 people dead.Four people have died in the Western Cape, while the North West and Northern Cape each recorded one death.The department's Legadima Leso says they are saddened. This illegal initiation schools don t follow the normal rules and guidelines. We have stated clearly in our guidelines that children must go for medical checkups and should drink plenty of water. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)